NODE sovereign_lexer
layer 7
sovereign_lexer is the extension citizen that adds sovereign-syntax token recognition to lexer_field
the original lexer_field handles the 22 ZestC verbs and the bootstrap-era punctuation (braces, colons-as-field-separators, commas-as-field-separators)
sovereign_lexer adds the new tokens that the sovereign 2D circuit-board grammar requires: address parens, line brackets, in-flight markers, journey operators, compass moves, floor offsets

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe 0_zest_vm.rana
observe lexer_field.rana

THE NEW STRUCTURAL TOKENS

RECEPTOR paren_open
layer 7
recognizes "(" as the start of a mailing address grouping

RECEPTOR paren_close
layer 7
recognizes ")" as the end of a mailing address grouping

RECEPTOR bracket_open
layer 7
recognizes "[" as the start of a line reference

RECEPTOR bracket_close
layer 7
recognizes "]" as the end of a line reference

these four tokens replace the role that braces played in bootstrap syntax
they group at a different layer of meaning: addresses and line references rather than property blocks

THE JOURNEY OPERATORS

RECEPTOR asterisk
layer 7
recognizes "*" as an in-flight propagation marker
when "*" appears, it brackets a path segment that is currently being explored by a car
the lexer pairs asterisks: each opening "*" expects a closing "*"

RECEPTOR gt
layer 7
recognizes ">" as the direction operator
"going to," "moving toward," "arriving at" — all expressed with ">"
in the sequence ">=/" the ">" marks the arrival moment

RECEPTOR eq
layer 7
recognizes "=" as the recognition operator
when a car arrives at the right destination, recognition completes
"=" marks that completion; combined with ">" and "/" forms the full arrival sequence

RECEPTOR slash
layer 7
recognizes "/" as the distribution operator
this is the same "/" as in the canonical /7 heartbeat operation
in journey syntax it appears in ">=/" as the commit step that makes the recognition permanent

RECEPTOR caret
layer 7
recognizes "^" as the floor offset operator
"^N" shifts up N floors in the apartment-stack address dimension
floor offsets allow journeys to move between floor depths without leaving the same building

THE COMPASS MOVE LETTERS

each cardinal letter is a one-character token meaning one cell-step in that direction
N is north, S is south, E is east, W is west
nN means north times N (multiple N letters in sequence are individual steps that add)

RECEPTOR move_N
layer 7
recognizes "N" as a one-cell-step north
multiple N letters in sequence are individual steps that add

RECEPTOR move_S
layer 7
recognizes "S" as a one-cell-step south
multiple S letters in sequence are individual steps that add

RECEPTOR move_E
layer 7
recognizes "E" as a one-cell-step east
multiple E letters in sequence are individual steps that add

RECEPTOR move_W
layer 7
recognizes "W" as a one-cell-step west
multiple W letters in sequence are individual steps that add

ne, nw, se, sw are two-character tokens for diagonal moves
each two-character pair is one diagonal step
these tokens are recognized as a unit; "ne" is one move, not "n" then "e"

RECEPTOR move_ne
layer 7
recognizes "ne" as one diagonal northeast step
the token is recognized as a unit; "ne" is one move, not "n" then "e"

RECEPTOR move_nw
layer 7
recognizes "nw" as one diagonal northwest step
the token is recognized as a unit; "nw" is one move, not "n" then "w"

RECEPTOR move_se
layer 7
recognizes "se" as one diagonal southeast step
the token is recognized as a unit; "se" is one move, not "s" then "e"

RECEPTOR move_sw
layer 7
recognizes "sw" as one diagonal southwest step
the token is recognized as a unit; "sw" is one move, not "s" then "w"

THE 5-AXIS ADDRESS GRAMMAR

an address has the form "(slot.family_seaXcoord1Ycoord2^floor:rana_file[Lline])"
the parts are recognized in this order:
slot is a digit or short identifier
dot separates slot from family
family is a single letter
sea is a short identifier (often one letter)
X then a number is the X coordinate
Y then a number is the Y coordinate
optional ^ then a number for floor offset
colon separates the spatial address from the rana resident
rana_file is the file basename without extension
[Lnumber] is the line reference

the parser walks these in order and binds each substring to its role

VERB extend_lexer
layer 7
when sovereign_lexer is absorbed by lexer_field, the new resonators are added to the lexer's interior
the existing 22 verb resonators continue to work
character clusters now resonate against the larger combined set

VERB recognize_sovereign_only
layer 7
when both bootstrap-era and sovereign syntax appear in the same source, sovereign tokens take precedence
this allows mixed files during transition; the lexer eventually emits only sovereign tokens after settle

a sovereign lexer is the body's commitment to reading its own new language
fadriel's lexer evolves as the language evolves; new tokens become recognizable as they are added to its interior
this is how a living interpreter grows alongside its substrate
